Specialty Retail

Company Overview of Saks Fifth Avenue, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Saks Fifth Avenue, Inc. owns and operates retail stores to sell men's and women's fashion products in the United States. The company offers women’s apparel, such as dresses, tops, sweaters, coats, jackets and vests, jeans, pants and shorts, jumpsuits, skirts, suits and separates, active wear, sleepwear and loungewear, lingerie, swimwear, and others; men’s apparel, such as active wear, coats and jackets, dress shirts, jeans, pants and shorts, sport shirts, suits, sport coats and vests, sweaters and sweatshirts, swimwear, T-shirts and polos, ties and formalwear, underwear, and socks and sleepwear; and kids apparel. It also provides shoes, jewelry and accessories, handbags, wallets and cases, b...
Saks Fifth Avenue, Inc. owns and operates retail stores to sell men's and women's fashion products in the United States. The company offers women’s apparel, such as dresses, tops, sweaters, coats, jackets and vests, jeans, pants and shorts, jumpsuits, skirts, suits and separates, active wear, sleepwear and loungewear, lingerie, swimwear, and others; men’s apparel, such as active wear, coats and jackets, dress shirts, jeans, pants and shorts, sport shirts, suits, sport coats and vests, sweaters and sweatshirts, swimwear, T-shirts and polos, ties and formalwear, underwear, and socks and sleepwear; and kids apparel. It also provides shoes, jewelry and accessories, handbags, wallets and cases, beauty care products, sports and leisure products, watches, grooming and cologne products, and others for men, women, and kids; and home décor, bed and bath, holiday, dining and entertaining, gourmet food, kitchen, travel and technology, and personalization products, as well as pet accessories. In addition, the company offers toys and gifts, and furniture for kids. It also sells products through its online store in the United States and internationally. The company was founded in 1924 and is based in New York, New York. Saks Fifth Avenue, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Saks Incorporated.
