Saks, Inc., originally Proffitt's Inc. until 1998, is a Fortune 1000 operator of high-end department stores in the United States under the nameplate Saks Fifth Avenue. It was founded in Birmingham, Alabama and is currently headquartered in New York City.



Contents


1 History

1.1 Proffitt's Inc.
1.2 Saks, Inc.
1.3 Divestments

